  "body": "<!-- Please use this template while reporting a bug and provide as much info as possible. Not doing so may result in your bug not being addressed in a timely manner. Thanks!\r\n\r\nIf the matter is security related, please disclose it privately via https://kubernetes.io/security/\r\n-->\r\n\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\n\r\ndir crated in /var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices would not be automatically removed.\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\n\r\nwhen a pod delete the, the dir would be removed\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n\r\ncreate a pod using csi raw block volume and delete it\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12230714/60653613-f4b2c280-9e7c-11e9-88ed-948f5e10692c.png)\r\n pod using pv-cb59bbc9-6195-49a0-b262-1adc9edeed1b actually has been deleted and the volume has been unmounted, but the dir still exists.\r\n\r\n![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/12230714/60658275-6a229100-9e85-11e9-97de-a79c26d58a87.png)\r\n\r\n/var/lib/kubelet/plugins/kubernetes.io/csi/volumeDevices/{pv}/data still exists\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`): 1.15\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n- OS (e.g: `cat /etc/os-release`):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Network plugin and version (if this is a network-related bug):\r\n- Others:\r\n",
